### Arquivo para a extensão "REST Client" do VS Code.
### API principal: http://localhost:3001 · Webhooks: http://localhost:3002

# ──────────────────────────── AUTENTICAÇÃO ────────────────────────────

### Login (admin)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "admin@crm.local", "password": "Admin@123" }

### Usuário atual
GET http://localhost:3001/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Renovar sessão (rotaciona o refresh token)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{login.response.body.refreshToken}}" }

# ──────────────────────────── TICKETS ────────────────────────────

### Listar tickets (filtros: status, platform, assignedTo=me|unassigned|<id>, search, dateFrom, dateTo)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/tickets?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Contadores por status
GET http://localhost:3001/api/tickets/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Buscar por nome/telefone/nº
GET http://localhost:3001/api/tickets?search=Maria
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Criar ticket manual (lead que ligou/veio à loja)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lead": { "name": "Cliente Balcão", "phone": "11912341234" },
  "message": "Procura hatch automático até 70 mil.",
  "vehicleText": "Hatch automático até R$ 70.000"
}

### Detalhe do ticket (troque :id)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/tickets/COLOQUE_O_ID_AQUI
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Atualizar status / prioridade / responsável
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/tickets/COLOQUE_O_ID_AQUI
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "status": "IN_PROGRESS", "priority": "HIGH" }

### Responder o cliente (registra 1ª resposta p/ SLA; assume ticket livre)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/tickets/COLOQUE_O_ID_AQUI/interactions
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "type": "AGENT_REPLY", "body": "Olá! O veículo está disponível sim." }

### Nota interna
POST http://localhost:3001/api/tickets/COLOQUE_O_ID_AQUI/interactions
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "type": "INTERNAL_NOTE", "body": "Cliente prefere contato após as 18h." }

# ──────────────────────────── WEBHOOKS (porta 3002) ────────────────────────────

### Lead OLX (token compartilhado — valor de dev em backend/.env)
POST http://localhost:3002/webhooks/olx
Content-Type: application/json
x-olx-token: dev-olx-token

< ./samples/olx-lead.json

### Lead Webmotors
POST http://localhost:3002/webhooks/webmotors
Content-Type: application/json
x-webmotors-token: dev-webmotors-token

< ./samples/webmotors-lead.json

### Lead Mercado Livre — exige HMAC-SHA256 do corpo em x-signature.
### Gere a assinatura com PowerShell (corpo EXATAMENTE igual ao enviado):
###   $body = [IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("samples/mercadolivre-lead.json")
###   $h = [Security.Cryptography.HMACSHA256]::new([Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes("dev-ml-secret"))
###   -join ($h.ComputeHash($body) | ForEach-Object ToString x2)
POST http://localhost:3002/webhooks/mercadolivre
Content-Type: application/json
x-signature: COLOQUE_A_ASSINATURA_AQUI

< ./samples/mercadolivre-lead.json

### Plataformas suportadas
GET http://localhost:3002/webhooks/platforms

# ──────────────────────────── FILA (admin) ────────────────────────────

### Eventos de webhook recebidos/processados/falhos
GET http://localhost:3001/api/webhook-events?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Reprocessar evento com falha
POST http://localhost:3001/api/webhook-events/COLOQUE_O_ID_AQUI/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
